body:
The following is legal FIRRTL by what the SFC accepts, but not by how the FIRRTL specification grammar is currently described:

```
circuit Foo:
  module Foo:
    input a: UInt<1>
    when a:
```

A variation of the above that has a statement after an empty `when`.

```
circuit Foo:
  module Foo:
    input a: UInt<1>
    when a:
    skip
```

This should either be allowed syntax or an error. I.e., either a `when` block must have a body or the body is optional.

Note: this construction is not reachable from Chisel as Chisel will always emit a `skip` for an empty `when` as shown in the following snippet:

```scala
//> using scala "2.13.10"
//> using lib "org.chipsalliance::chisel::6.0.0-M2"
//> using plugin "org.chipsalliance:::chisel-plugin::6.0.0-M2"
//> using options "-unchecked", "-deprecation", "-language:reflectiveCalls", "-feature", "-Xcheckinit", "-Ywarn-dead-code", "-Ywarn-unused", "-Ymacro-annotations"

import chisel3._
import circt.stage.ChiselStage

class Foo extends RawModule {
  val a = IO(Input(Bool()))
  when (a) {
  }
}

object Main extends App {
  println(ChiselStage.emitCHIRRTL(new Foo))
}
```
